WEBVTT



00:00:09.984 --> 00:00:13.248
Welcome to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.

00:00:13.376 --> 00:00:17.472
Our mission is to develop fully devoted followers of Christ.

00:00:17.920 --> 00:00:25.984
Thanks for tuning in on today's episode. we are excited to have Melanie Grant reading Psalm 143 as part of our Psalms Project journey.

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:32.384
Psalm 143.

00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:34.464
A psalm of David.

00:00:35.584 --> 00:00:37.952
O Lord, hear my prayer.

00:00:37.824 --> 00:00:40.192
Listen to my cry for mercy.

00:00:40.544 --> 00:00:44.288
In your faithfulness and righteousness come to my relief

00:00:44.448 --> 00:00:47.040
Do not bring your servant into judgment.

00:00:47.040 --> 00:00:50.112
For no one living is righteous before you.

00:00:50.560 --> 00:00:52.640
The enemy pursues me.

00:00:52.576 --> 00:00:54.784
He crushes me to the ground.

00:00:55.008 --> 00:01:01.120
He makes me dwell in darkness like those long dead, so my spirit grows faint within me.

00:01:01.184 --> 00:01:03.904
My heart within me is dismayed.

00:01:04.512 --> 00:01:07.104
I remember the days of long ago.

00:01:07.104 --> 00:01:11.200
I meditate on all your works and consider what your hands have done.

00:01:11.232 --> 00:01:13.664
I spread out my hands to you.

00:01:13.632 --> 00:01:17.120
My soul thirsts for you like a parched land.

00:01:17.664 --> 00:01:19.904
Answer me quickly, o Lord.

00:01:19.808 --> 00:01:21.760
My spirit fails.

00:01:21.984 --> 00:01:26.368
Do not hide your face from me, or I will be like those who go down to the pit.

00:01:27.072 --> 00:01:30.720
Let the morning bring me word of your unfailing love

00:01:30.496 --> 00:01:32.704
For I have put my trust in you.

00:01:32.832 --> 00:01:34.944
Show me the way I should go.

00:01:35.040 --> 00:01:37.536
For to you I lift up my soul.

00:01:38.048 --> 00:01:42.656
Rescue me from my enemies, O Lord, for I hide myself in you.

00:01:43.328 --> 00:01:45.344
Teach me to do your will.

00:01:45.152 --> 00:01:46.944
For you are my God.

00:01:46.912 --> 00:01:50.336
May your good spirit lead me on level ground.

00:01:51.040 --> 00:01:54.496
For your name's sake, o Lord, preserve my life.

00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:57.312
In your righteousness bring me out of trouble.

00:01:57.664 --> 00:02:02.656
In your unfailing love, silence my enemies, destroy all my foes.

00:02:02.464 --> 00:02:04.256
For I am your servant.

00:02:05.184 --> 00:02:08.992
Seems to me that David has reached the point of despair.

00:02:09.632 --> 00:02:11.168
Have you ever been there?

00:02:11.456 --> 00:02:13.280
Are you there right now?

00:02:14.752 --> 00:02:16.864
When calamity strikes

00:02:17.440 --> 00:02:22.464
Are you able to direct your thoughts to God and keep from becoming despondent?

00:02:23.616 --> 00:02:26.304
What sorts of things do you focus on?

00:02:26.816 --> 00:02:28.928
In order to be able to

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:31.648
Keep yourself from a place of despair.

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:47.840
We hope this message was encouraging to you. If you would like this kind of content delivered directly to you, consider subscribing to our channel.

00:02:47.872 --> 00:02:57.376
If you'd like more information about our church, please visit us on the web at canopyroads.org. And thanks for listening to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.
